<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-08-19T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-08-19T21:00:00-05:00" n="185" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d185">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/221:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-08-20T10:00:00+08:00">August 20, 1929—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 20—7:04 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>737. My 730, August 18, 6 [<hi rend="italic">4</hi>] p.m. Following from
                            American Consul at Harbin: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“August 19, 4 p.m. Customs reports from Taheiho state Chinese
                                    military are about to evacuate from that place and that raiding
                                    parties, presumably Soviet, are crossing the Amur and pillaging
                                    on Chinese side.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>